<paragraph blockId="39.[155,772,349,1905]" box="[155,253,349,370]" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">
<emphasis box="[155,253,349,370]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[155,772,349,1905]" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">
<bibRefCitation author="Bergh R" box="[155,318,380,402]" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" pagination="58 - 61" refId="ref53810" refString="Bergh R. 1877 a. Malacologische Untersuchungen. In: Semper C, ed. Reisen im Archipel der Philippinen, theil 2, heft 10. Wiesbaden: Kreidel, 495 - 546, plates 58 - 61." type="book chapter" year="1877">Bergh (1877a)</bibRefCitation>
described the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergh" authorityYear="1877" box="[563,663,380,401]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Thordisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[563,663,380,401]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Thordisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on 
<taxonomicName authority="Bergh, 1877" authorityName="Bergh" authorityYear="1877" box="[155,553,410,432]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Thordisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="maculigera">
<emphasis box="[155,393,410,431]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Thordisa maculigera</emphasis>
Bergh, 1877
</taxonomicName>
, but at the same time mentioned that 
<taxonomicName authority="Alder &amp; Hancock, 1864" authorityName="Alder &amp; Hancock" authorityYear="1864" class="Gastropoda" family="Dorididae" genus="Doris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis box="[408,551,441,463]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Doris villosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Alder J &amp; Hancock A" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" pagination="113 - 147" refId="ref53398" refString="Alder J, Hancock A. 1864. Notice of a collection of nudibranchiate Mollusca made in India by Water Elliot Esq., with descriptions of several new genera and species. Transactions of the Zoological Society of London 5: 113 - 147, plates 28 - 33." type="journal article" year="1864">Alder &amp; Hancock, 1864</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, also belongs to this genus. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Bergh R" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" pagination="58 - 61" refId="ref53810" refString="Bergh R. 1877 a. Malacologische Untersuchungen. In: Semper C, ed. Reisen im Archipel der Philippinen, theil 2, heft 10. Wiesbaden: Kreidel, 495 - 546, plates 58 - 61." type="book chapter" year="1877">Bergh (1877a)</bibRefCitation>
the main distinctive feature of this genus is the presence of elongate tubercles on the dorsum and pectinate outermost lateral teeth. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bergh R" box="[617,771,564,586]" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" pagination="103 - 144" refId="ref54306" refString="Bergh R. 1891. Die cryptobranchiaten Dorididen. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere 6: 103 - 144." type="journal article" year="1891">Bergh (1891)</bibRefCitation>
regarded 
<taxonomicName authority="Ihering, 1886" authorityName="Ihering" authorityYear="1886" box="[274,542,594,616]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Etidoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[274,364,594,615]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Etidoris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ihering" box="[380,542,594,616]" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" pagination="223 - 240" refId="ref56649" refString="Ihering von H. 1886. Zur Kenntniss der Nudibranchien der brasilianischen Kuste. Jahrbucher der Deutschen Malakozoologischen Gesellschaft 13: 223 - 240, pl. 9." type="journal article" year="1886">Ihering, 1886</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergh" authorityYear="1877" box="[155,255,625,646]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Thordisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[155,255,625,646]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Thordisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bergh R" box="[269,419,625,647]" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref54555" refString="Bergh R. 1905. Die Opisthobranchiata der Siboga-Expedition. In: Weber M, ed. Uitkomsten op Zoologisch, Botanisch, Oceanographisch en Geologisch Gebied verzameld in Nederlandsch Oost-Indie 1899 - 1900 aan boord H. M. Siboga onder commando van Luitenant ter zee Ie kl. G. F. Tydeman, Vol. 50. Leiden: Brill, 1 - 248, plates 1 - 20." type="book chapter" year="1905">Bergh (1905)</bibRefCitation>
added the new species 
<taxonomicName authority="Bergh, 1905" authorityName="Bergh" authorityYear="1905" class="Gastropoda" family="Dorididae" genus="Doris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">T. carinata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bergh R" box="[213,354,656,678]" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref54555" refString="Bergh R. 1905. Die Opisthobranchiata der Siboga-Expedition. In: Weber M, ed. Uitkomsten op Zoologisch, Botanisch, Oceanographisch en Geologisch Gebied verzameld in Nederlandsch Oost-Indie 1899 - 1900 aan boord H. M. Siboga onder commando van Luitenant ter zee Ie kl. G. F. Tydeman, Vol. 50. Leiden: Brill, 1 - 248, plates 1 - 20." type="book chapter" year="1905">Bergh, 1905</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergh" authorityYear="1905" box="[366,457,656,678]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Thordisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tristis">
<emphasis box="[366,457,656,678]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">T. tristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergh" authorityYear="1905" box="[469,570,656,678]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Thordisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hilaris">
<emphasis box="[469,570,656,678]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">T. hilaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and with a question mark 
<taxonomicName box="[272,404,686,708]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Thordisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="maculosa">
<emphasis box="[272,404,686,708]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">T. maculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the list of species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergh" authorityYear="1877" box="[663,763,686,707]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Thordisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[663,763,686,707]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Thordisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and designated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergh" authorityYear="1877" box="[340,491,717,739]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Thordisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="maculigera">
<emphasis box="[340,491,717,739]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">T. maculigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[576,625,718,739]" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[155,772,349,1905]" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ev. Marcus &amp; Er. Marcus" authorityYear="1967" box="[322,408,749,770]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Nuvuca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[322,408,749,770]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Nuvuca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus Ev &amp; Marcus Er" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" pagination="597 - 628" refId="ref57170" refString="Marcus Ev, Marcus Er. 1967 a. Opisthobranchs from the southwestern Caribbean Sea. Biological Investigations of the Deep Sea, 33. Bulletin of Marine Science 17: 597 - 628." type="journal article" year="1967">Marcus &amp; Marcus (1967a)</bibRefCitation>
on the basis of a single specimen of the new species 
<taxonomicName authority="Ev. Marcus &amp; Er. Marcus, 1967" authorityName="Ev. Marcus &amp; Er. Marcus" authorityYear="1967" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Nuvuca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lurca">
<emphasis box="[303,456,809,831]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Nuvuca lurca</emphasis>
Ev. Marcus &amp; Er. Marcus, 1967
</taxonomicName>
. According to these authors, the diagnostic features of this genus are: strongly spiculate body, unequal papillae on the dorsum, smooth labial cuticle, inner radular teeth with a short base and long cusp and pectinate outer teeth; a dart or copulatory spine joined to the male atrium; penis unarmed. Examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[289,386,1024,1046]" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">holotype</typeStatus>
of the type species revealed the presence of large dorsal papillae similar to those present in other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergh" authorityYear="1877" box="[460,560,1085,1106]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Thordisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[460,560,1085,1106]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Thordisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The only remarkable difference between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ev. Marcus &amp; Er. Marcus" authorityYear="1967" box="[439,525,1117,1138]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Nuvuca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[439,525,1117,1138]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Nuvuca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[587,695,1116,1137]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Thoridisa</emphasis>
is the absence of jaws in the former. This could be due to either interspecific variation or to Marcus &amp; Marcus’s (1967a) neglecting to find this structure. Unfortunately, the parts of the foregut of the 
<typeStatus box="[619,716,1238,1260]" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">holotype</typeStatus>
dissected by Marcus &amp; Marcus are not preserved with the rest of the specimen, and re-examination is not possible. Because the rest of the external and anatomical features of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ev. Marcus &amp; Er. Marcus" authorityYear="1967" box="[288,374,1362,1383]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Nuvuca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[288,374,1362,1383]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Nuvuca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are identical to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergh" authorityYear="1877" box="[665,764,1361,1382]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Thordisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[665,764,1361,1382]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Thordisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, they are here regarded as synonyms.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[155,772,349,1905]" lastBlockId="39.[819,1434,196,310]" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus Er &amp; Marcus Ev" box="[180,507,1423,1445]" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" pagination="155 - 179" refId="ref57232" refString="Marcus Er, Marcus Ev. 1970 a. Opisthobranch mollusks from the Southern tropical Pacific. Pacific Science 24: 155 - 179." type="journal article" year="1970">Marcus &amp; Marcus (1970a)</bibRefCitation>
described the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Er. Marcus &amp; Ev. Marcus" authorityYear="1970" box="[155,257,1453,1474]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Pupsikus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[155,257,1453,1474]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Pupsikus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the new species 
<taxonomicName authority="Ev. Marcus &amp; Er. Marcus, 1970" authorityName="Ev. Marcus &amp; Er. Marcus" authorityYear="1970" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Pupsikus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pinguis">
<emphasis box="[576,771,1453,1475]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Pupsikus pinguis</emphasis>
Ev. Marcus &amp; Er. Marcus, 1970
</taxonomicName>
. According to these authors, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Er. Marcus &amp; Ev. Marcus" authorityYear="1970" box="[259,361,1514,1535]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Pupsikus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[259,361,1514,1535]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Pupsikus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by having a ridge connecting the tentacles with the foot, labial armature with rodlets and ‘a radula containing denticulate lateral and feathered marginal teeth’. The prostate is voluminous, the penis is armed with hooks and there is an accessory gland with a copulatory spine. The ridges that connect the oral tentacles and the foot in the single preserved specimen examined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus Er &amp; Marcus Ev" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" pagination="155 - 179" refId="ref57232" refString="Marcus Er, Marcus Ev. 1970 a. Opisthobranch mollusks from the Southern tropical Pacific. Pacific Science 24: 155 - 179." type="journal article" year="1970">Marcus &amp; Marcus (1970a)</bibRefCitation>
, are probably an artifact of observation. A re-examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[487,584,1790,1812]" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">holotype</typeStatus>
has revealed an oral morphology similar to that of other cryptobranch dorids. No trace of the ridge mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus Er &amp; Marcus Ev" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" pagination="155 - 179" refId="ref57232" refString="Marcus Er, Marcus Ev. 1970 a. Opisthobranch mollusks from the Southern tropical Pacific. Pacific Science 24: 155 - 179." type="journal article" year="1970">Marcus &amp; Marcus (1970a)</bibRefCitation>
has been found. The specimen was dissected and no anatomical information could be extracted from it, but the drawings and descriptions of 
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus Er &amp; Marcus Ev" box="[819,1121,257,279]" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" pagination="155 - 179" refId="ref57232" refString="Marcus Er, Marcus Ev. 1970 a. Opisthobranch mollusks from the Southern tropical Pacific. Pacific Science 24: 155 - 179." type="journal article" year="1970">Marcus &amp; Marcus (1970a)</bibRefCitation>
are sufficient to identify it as a member of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergh" authorityYear="1877" box="[1127,1226,288,309]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Thordisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="39" pageNumber="574" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1127,1226,288,309]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="574">Thordisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
